tandings of gender, care and subjectivity, becoming a mother remains one of the most personally and culturally significant moments in a woman’s life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMother and childzAustraliaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMother and childzAustraliaxHistoryy21st century. 0aMotherhoodzAustraliaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotherhoodzAustraliaxHistoryy21st century. 0aMotherszAustraliaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotherszAustraliaxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aAustralian history.  abirth.  achildrearing.  afeminist history.  agender studies.  ahistory of motherhood.  amaternal studies.  amatrescence.  aoral history.  apregnancy.  awomen’s history.1 aLeahy, Carla Pascoe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616121540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526161215423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526161215/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles